    {
      "text": "A child presents with erythematous scaly patches in the perioral region, mucosal ulcers, and impaired epithelial wound healing. The most likely mineral deficiency associated with this condition is",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Iron deficiency"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Zinc deficiency"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Calcium deficiency"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Copper deficiency"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: B) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39ecb6e07416927772029550b7e74a\">Zinc</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The above scenario is suggestive of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39ecb6e07416927772029550b7e74a\">Zinc</span> deficiency.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Zinc <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">Deficiency</span> Manifestations:</strong>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Poor Wound Healing</li>\n\t\t<li>Skin Lesions: Rashes, dermatitis, and hyperkeratosis.</li>\n\t\t<li>Alopecia.</li>\n\t\t<li>Impaired Spermatogenesis.</li>\n\t\t<li>Immune Dysfunction: <strong>Decreased T and B <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c605d4126116927771916c2002638e\">lymphocyte</span> counts</strong>; impaired <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2748357f451692777191377abbe2a6\">macrophage</span> function.</li>\n\t\t<li>Neurological Effects: Depression, dementia, and other psychiatric disorders.\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li>Zinc also forms <strong>plaques with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51ad856e041692777181f80c9d507a\">amyloid</span> in Alzheimer's disease</strong>.</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li>Acrodermatitis Enteropathica: A genetic condition characterized by:\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li>Inflammation around the mouth, nose, and fingers.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Diarrhea.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Hair loss.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Ophthalmoplegia and hypogonadism.</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Iron <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> (Option A):</strong> Iron <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> typically causes symptoms like pallor, fatigue, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"395e767e0f1692777188ec3554bc15\">glossitis</span> but does not result in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a37fd1603c1692777198f87a4a51dc\">scaly</span> patches or impaired wound healing.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Calcium <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> (Option C):</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54de8b79a91692777183e608bc0dd4\">Calcium</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> primarily affects bone health, leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3bbd4ac09b16927771974d75a8b355\">rickets</span> in children or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fc9f873eb21692777194d3feb4e68d\">osteomalacia</span> in adults. Skin or mucosal symptoms are not characteristic.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Copper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> (Option D): </strong>Copper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> can cause anemia, neutropenia, and neurological deficits. It is associated with poor <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"67e237a57c16927771859803f93ab3\">connective</span> tissue integrity (e.g., <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12bc987eb11692777190686c0f0c75\">kinky hair</span> in Menkes disease) but does not cause <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a37fd1603c1692777198f87a4a51dc\">scaly</span> patches or mucosal ulcers.</p>",
