      "text": "Which of the following minerals is best known for insulin secretion stabilisation?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Cadmium"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Copper"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Iron"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Zinc"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option: D) Zinc</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Zinc is an essential <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d33c06dca716927772001536d7e639\">trace mineral</span> that plays a crucial role in numerous biological processes, including <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b47c9c6144169277719010eaa1a0ee\">insulin</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9b0ae3750916927771986c15d4ff4d\">secretion</span> and stabilization. It is involved in the synthesis, storage, and release of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b47c9c6144169277719010eaa1a0ee\">insulin</span> from pancreatic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"806eb8418c16927771822855b56695\">beta</span> cells. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39ecb6e07416927772029550b7e74a\">Zinc</span> also helps in maintaining the structure and stability of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b47c9c6144169277719010eaa1a0ee\">insulin</span> molecules.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Zinc</strong>:</p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:615px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Dietary Sources</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Grains, beans, nuts, cheese, meat, shellfish.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Therapeutic Use</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Zinc reduces <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5fcb9396d1169277718069dd7fa788\">absorption</span> in Wilson’s disease.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Zinc-Dependent Enzymes</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Carboxypeptidase</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Carbonic anhydrase</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Alkaline phosphatase</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Lactate dehydrogenase</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Ethanol dehydrogenase</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Glutamate dehydrogenase</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>RNA <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d419920a6616927771969805c3d65d\">polymerase</span> (required for protein biosynthesis)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Functions</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Antioxidant RoleExtracellular <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7d51964ce51692777199dedcf19fc3\">superoxide</span> dismutase is zinc-dependent, contributing to zinc’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1f3c08447d16927771819ccd566468\">antioxidant</span> properties.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Insulin and ZincZinc stabilizes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b47c9c6144169277719010eaa1a0ee\">insulin</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"806eb8418c16927771822855b56695\">beta</span> cells of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e2fe8c6c116927771946fb9a8adb0\">pancreas</span> but is not present in released insulin.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Taste Sensation Gusten, a zinc-containing protein in saliva, is important for taste sensation.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Deficiency Manifestations</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Poor wound healing</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Skin lesions, hyperkeratosis, dermatitis, alopecia</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Impaired spermatogenesis</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Reduced T and B <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c605d4126116927771916c2002638e\">lymphocyte</span> numbers, impaired <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2748357f451692777191377abbe2a6\">macrophage</span> function</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Psychiatric disorders: depression, dementia, and cognitive decline (e.g., Alzheimer's)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Acrodermatitis Enteropathica</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Acrodermatitis (inflammation around mouth, nose, fingers, etc.)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Diarrhea, alopecia, ophthalmoplegia, hypogonadism</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Toxicity Manifestations</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Chronic Toxicity: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">Gastric</span> ulcers, pancreatitis, anemia, nausea, vomiting, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10e2dee19e1692777196673db90c23\">pulmonary</span> fibrosis</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Acute Toxicity: Fever, excessive salivation, headache, anemia</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Cadmium (Option A)</strong> is a toxic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e8ada09fa1692777189bfbace851a\">heavy metal</span> that can have detrimental effects on health, including disrupting various <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6c2c85ae6b16927771950809419a59\">physiological</span> processes.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Copper (Option B)</strong> is an essential <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d33c06dca716927772001536d7e639\">trace mineral</span> that plays a role in various bodily functions, including the formation of red blood cells and maintaining <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"67e237a57c16927771859803f93ab3\">connective</span> tissues. While it is involved in several <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11d4157da4169277718762144a4fe7\">enzymatic</span> reactions.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Iron (Option C)</strong> is vital for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d27c5d96b416927771941e7efc4010\">oxygen transport</span> in the blood and is a key component of hemoglobin.</p>",
