    {
      "text": "Menke's disease is due to a deficiency of:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Zinc"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Copper"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Iron"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Magnesium"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer: B) Copper</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Menke's disease occurs due to a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> due to a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"359a8718a61692777185568ac80abb\">defect</span> in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5fcb9396d1169277718069dd7fa788\">absorption</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> from the intestine.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Menkes disease (also called <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12bc987eb11692777190686c0f0c75\">kinky hair</span> disease) </strong>is a rare, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dd35346fc716927772029e2f0bb10f\">X-linked</span> genetic disorder caused by a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5fcb9396d1169277718069dd7fa788\">absorption</span> due to mutations in the <strong>ATP7A gene.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Brittle, kinky hair</li>\n\t<li>Growth failure</li>\n\t<li>Neurodegeneration (seizures, developmental delay)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Pathophysiology:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Copper is essential for enzymes like <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"60f3918aab1692777191e8bde76c5f\">lysyl</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4a14dfa14e1692777194882f818d87\">oxidase</span> (collagen cross-linking) and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"29e8e2a5dd16927771855db589c581\">cytochrome</span> c <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4a14dfa14e1692777194882f818d87\">oxidase</span> (cellular respiration).</li>\n\t<li>Impaired <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> transport leads to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8f2e7fd96116927771995b451b5c90\">systemic</span> deficiency, affecting <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0f160e4e42169277718771b715516a\">enzyme</span> functions.</li>\n\t<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> gets trapped in the metallothionine present in the intestinal cells.</li>\n\t<li>This prevents the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> from being absorbed into the bloodstream.</li>\n\t<li>The symptoms of Menke's disease include <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10c83adb331692777197f775bec1aa\">reduced</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a0e40688fa169277719572bdb48c92\">plasma</span> and urine, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fa15f2737616927771864ea2681ae1\">depigmentation</span> of hair.</li>\n\t<li>Can be treated by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b5fb2b56416927771858f02fd5508\">copper</span> replacement therapy.</li>\n</ul>",
