          "text": "lodine"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Copper"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) Calcium</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Minerals are crucial for normal growth and body maintenance. Those required in amounts greater than 100 mg/day are called <strong>macrominerals</strong> or <strong>major elements</strong>, while those needed in smaller amounts (less than 100 mg/day) are known as <strong>microminerals</strong>, <strong>trace elements</strong>, or <strong>minor elements</strong>.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Calcium</strong> is classified as a <strong>macromineral</strong> (major element), not a micromineral. It is required by the body in large amounts (greater than 100 mg/day) for functions like bone formation, muscle contraction, and nerve transmission.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:NaN\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Macrominerals</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Microminerals (Trace elements)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Calcium <strong>(Option A)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Magnesium</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Phosphorus</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Sodium</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Potassium</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Chloride</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Sulfur</li>\n\t\t\t</ol>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Iron</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Iodine <strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Copper <strong>(Option D ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Manganese</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Zinc</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Molybdenum</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Selenium <strong>(Option B ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Fluoride</li>\n\t\t\t</ol>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
